// logdrop — Roadmap page
// v2.0 feature plan, open tasks, and a status callout.
// ============================================================

:INFO
v2.0 Roadmap
CENTER
v2.0 is a significant rethink of logdrop's internals. The headline feature is multi-source
fan-in: instead of piping one process, you define a set of named sources (files, processes,
sockets) and logdrop merges them into a single enriched stream.

This page is the canonical planning document. It is generated from the repo — every merged PR
that closes a roadmap task updates this page automatically via Slatesource.

:NOW
v2.0 in active design — no release date committed yet. Breaking changes expected.

:CHECKLIST
Core Architecture
[x] Replace line-reader with io_uring-backed reader (Linux) / kqueue (macOS)
[x] Internal event bus (replace direct stdout writes)
[ ] Multi-source fan-in engine
[ ] Unified source registry (file, process, UNIX socket, TCP)
[ ] Hot-reload config without process restart

:CHECKLIST
Sinks & Outputs
[x] Refactor sink interface to async trait
[ ] Grafana Loki sink (HTTP + gRPC)
[ ] OpenTelemetry OTLP exporter
[ ] File rotation sink (size + time policies)
[ ] Dead-letter queue for failed sink writes

:CHECKLIST
Filters & Transforms
[x] Filter DSL prototype (internal)
[ ] Ship filter DSL as stable public API
[ ] Field extraction (dot-path syntax: event.user.id)
[ ] Redaction rules (PII scrubbing before forwarding)
[ ] Sampling (e.g. keep 1-in-N DEBUG lines)

:CHECKLIST
Developer Experience
[ ] logdrop.toml config file with JSON Schema
[ ] Shell completions (bash, zsh, fish)
[ ] --dry-run mode (validate config, print parsed events, exit)
[ ] Homebrew formula
[ ] Official Docker image on GHCR

:NOTE
v2.0 will not ship until the multi-source fan-in engine is solid and the filter DSL is stable.
There is no fixed date. If you are building on logdrop in production, stay on the latest v1.x
tag — it receives backported security fixes for at least 12 months after v2.0 ships.

:QUOTE
Every new capability has to earn its place in a 5 MB binary.

:PATH
Design phase → Implementation
Architecture decisions open for community input until v2.0-alpha

